Now, I said that Wikipedia has a very nice page that mentions

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
all the types of hands, and it also gives the percentages for each hand.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:11.000
That is, out of all the possible poker hands,

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:14.000
what percentage are a straight flush, four of a kind,

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:16.000
full house, and so on, so here's the percentages.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:19.000
We see that about half the hands don't have anything.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:21.000
They're just the high card with no pairs or anything else.

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:27.000
And then 42% are pairs, and then less for each of those.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:31.000
And we see the percentages align with the actual poker values.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:36.000
That is, the most rare hand, the straight flush, is the highest ranking.

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:39.000
The next most rare hand, four of a kind, is the next highest ranking,

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:42.000
and the most common is the least highest, so that makes sense.

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:46.000
Poker is a sensible game from the point of view of probability.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:50.000
Now, one thing we can do is see if we can duplicate this type of table.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:54.000
